    "explanation": "<p>Here's a breakdown of the matching and why the correct answer is <strong>Option C</strong>: </p>\n\n<p>Let's analyze each compound and its corresponding use:</p>\n\n<p>(A) <strong>Sodium perborate</strong> is a common ingredient in laundry detergents and is known for its bleaching and stain-removing properties. Therefore, it's linked to <strong>(R) Milk bleaching agent</strong>. </p>\n\n<p>(B) <strong>Chlorine</strong> is a powerful disinfectant and is widely used in water treatment, sanitation, and cleaning.  It's a strong disinfectant, so it matches <strong>(1) Disinfectant</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>(C) <strong>Bithional</strong> is an antiseptic agent commonly found in soaps and personal care products. It helps prevent the growth of bacteria and fungi. Therefore, it matches <strong>(2) Antiseptic</strong>. </p>\n\n<p>(D) <strong>Potassium stearate</strong> is a major component of soap. It acts as a surfactant, helping to remove dirt and grease through emulsification. This matches <strong>(4) Soap</strong>. </p>\n\n<p>Therefore, the correct matching is: </p>\n\n<p>A - 3, B - 1, C - 2, D - 4</p>\n\n<p>This corresponds to <strong>Option C</strong>. </p>\n\n<p></p>",
